javax.time.calendrical

Interface TemporalUnit.PeriodBetween

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Temporal.MinusAdjuster, Temporal.PlusAdjuster
    Enclosing interface:
    TemporalUnit

    public static interface TemporalUnit.PeriodBetween
extends Temporal.PlusAdjuster, Temporal.MinusAdjuster
    Simple period representing the amount of time between two temporal objects.

    This interface is the return type from TemporalUnit.between(R, R). It represents an amount of time measured in a single unit. It can be queried for the amount and unit, or added directly to another date-time: 

      date = date.minus(MONTHS.between(start, end));

    Implementation notes

    This interface must be implemented with care to ensure other classes operate correctly. All implementations that can be instantiated must be final, immutable and thread-safe.
